  "research_html": "<div class=\"research-section\">\n<p class=\"research-text\">No substantive information exists for a philosophical treatise titled <strong>On the Nature of Being</strong> attributed to an Early Greek philosopher named Thearidas. The name Thearidas does not appear in canonical Presocratic sources, and the term used to describe the work indicates a fragment or excerpt, not a formal title. The attribution is therefore unverified. The content and themes of this purported work are unknown, and there is no known manuscript tradition. The description of the work as a single passage aligns with the title&#x27;s meaning of &quot;fragment,&quot; suggesting a completely lost or spurious reference. Without corroborating evidence, the work&#x27;s historical or philosophical influence cannot be established.</p>\n</div>",
  "rows": [
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "reference": "201 (15t)",
      "text": "Περὶ φύσεως Clem. Strom. 5.133.1 p. 416 St. Θεαρίδας δὲ ἐν τῷ Περὶ φύσεως γράφει· ἁ ἀρχὰ τῶν ὄντων, ἀρχὰ μὲν ὄντως ἀληθινά, μία· κείνα γὰρ ἐν ἀρχᾷ τέ ἐστιν ἓν καὶ μόνον.",
